    <abstract>The scholar Sun Xingyan 孫星衍 (1753-1818) worked together with Ruan Yuan in those years and compiled an extensive list of stone inscriptions in the entire country 
        under the title Huanyu fangbei lu 寰宇訪碑録 (Record of enquiries into stelae in the whole world; preface 1802). (Huanyu fangbei lu by Sun Xingyan (1753/5-1818). (Shike shiliao xinbian) 1-26-10873b.)
        He says that four different sutra texts, written in standard script, exist on Mount Gang and gives the date.  
        This information does not go beyond what Ruan Yuan had said. (LL)</abstract>
